description: The Creality Ender 3 is a popular and affordable 3D printer that is great for beginners and experienced makers alike. With a build volume of 220 x 220 x 250 mm, it can handle a wide range of projects.

The Ultimaker 3 is a high-end 3D printer that delivers professional-grade results. With dual extrusion, it can print with two materials at once, allowing for highly complex designs. The build volume is 215 x 215 x 300 mm.

The Prusa i3 MK3S+ is a highly-regarded 3D printer kit that offers excellent build quality and reliability. It features a large build volume of 25 x 21 x 21 cm and comes with a variety of upgrades that make it even better than its predecessor, the MK3S.

The LulzBot Mini 2 is a compact and versatile 3D printer that is great for both beginners and experienced users. It features a build volume of 16 x 16 x 18 cm and comes with an automatic bed leveling system that makes setup a breeze.
The MakerBot Replicator + is great 3d printer for daily home use.
